com.coveros.selenified.element.check

Interface Excludes

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AssertExcludes, VerifyExcludes

    public interface Excludes
    Excludes extends Check to provide some additional checking capabilities. It will handle all checks performed on the actual element. These asserts are custom to the framework, and in addition to providing easy object oriented capabilities, they take screenshots with each check to provide additional traceability, and assist in troubleshooting and debugging failing tests. Excludes checks that elements don't have a particular value associated to them.
    Version:
    3.1.0
    Author:
    Max Saperstone
